adviseScripts.text: Trainer! Here's a gift for you!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Biscuit hands me a ball.
Throw the ball as far as you can.
Thank you.
It's a gift... How could you throw...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I'm guessing you don't like it?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I threw it because I want to play with you.
Oh, I see!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: This is my favorite ball, hehe. I thought it'd be great if you have one too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I'm so glad that you like it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Shall we play ball games together?
Ball games...!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Biscuit's tail wags rapidly.
Yes!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I play ball games with Biscuit.
Excuse me... Trainer!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Uh, isn't it... stifling to stay indoors today?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Shall we go out for a walk?
Shall I open the window for you?
As expected from you, Trainer! You know me so well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, this is great.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Let's go out now!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: No, I didn't mean to say that it's stuffy here...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I... want to go out for a walk...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Can't we do that?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I go for a walk with Biscuit.

Nom nom nom nom!
Nom nom nom nom!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I take a look at what Biscuit is eating.
Uh... This is sweet potato-flavored Splendamin...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: W-would you like to have some?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Sure, thank you.
I'm good. You can have it all.
You're really going to eat with me...?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Oh, it's not that I don't want to share it...!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Biscuit's tail droops low.
I'm happy that we can eat together... Hehe...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Really?! You don't need to stand on ceremony.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Biscuit's tail starts spinning like a propeller.
Hehehe...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Then I'll dig in now, Trainer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I feed Biscuit sweet potato-flavored Splendamin.
Trainer, which do you prefer?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Sweet snacks or savory snacks?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Sweet snacks are the best.
Savory snacks are the best.
You think so too, Trainer?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Hooray for sweet snacks!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Just thinking of sweet snacks makes me happy...!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: *Drool* Now I'm craving it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Savory snacks?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Uh... I heard too much salt isn't good for you...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I prefer sweet snacks.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Well, they say too much sugar isn't healthy as well, but the sweetness really cheers me up!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I head out with Biscuit to buy snacks.
Trainer, what kind of weather do you like?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Rainy weather.
Sunny weather.
Oh... I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I don't like rainy days, because I get wet while taking a walk...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Indeed! Sunny days are the best, right?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: The air is refreshing, and the ground is clean!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: It's perfect for all sorts of walks! I love it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I check the weather forecast with Biscuit.
Poli and Jackal are so nice.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Just looking at them makes me feel... How should I put it...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: It makes me feel acknowledged, so I feel great!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Is that the so-called bond between dogs?
That's the so-called bond between Nikkes, isn't it?
You're incredible, Trainer. You saw through it right away!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, dogs are telepathic with each other!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Uh... Um, I guess you can put it that way...!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I meant to say that dogs can understand each other...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Hehe...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: ... I want to tell her that Poli and Jackal are not real dogs, but I hold myself back.
Trainer!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Biscuit stares at me intently.
Hehehe!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: She wags her tail furiously!
Stroke her head.
Grab her tail.
Hehehe, you know me well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I just thought it'd be great if you can stroke my head.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Can you do it for a little longer?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Uh? What? Hmm? Trai... Trainer? Why did you suddenly grab my tail...?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Uh... I wanted you to stroke my head.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I rub Biscuit's head hastily.
Trainer!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Biscuit holds out a frisbee.
Let's play together!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Open the window and throw the frisbee far away.
Lightly toss the frisbee toward the door.
That... That far...?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I'll be back...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: *Chomp*
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Biscuit runs over and catches the frisbee with her mouth.
Haha! I did great, right?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Can you throw it again?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I play frisbee with Biscuit.
Trainer, if you were to raise a puppy,
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: what kind of puppy would you want?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: A puppy like you.
A puppy like Poli.
Really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: You're fond of puppies like me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Hehehe. I'm also fond of humans like you, Trainer!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: A puppy like Poli would be adorable.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Right. Poli is cute, so you'd obviously want to raise a puppy like her.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Um... I don't know why but... I feel a bit sad...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I teach Biscuit the things one should know before raising a puppy.
Trainer, what kind of scent do you like?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: The musty smell of a dog coming home from a walk on a rainy day.
The fresh smell of a dog right out of the shower.
... What?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Uh... You like that scent?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: ... Not kidding?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Wow! You're right!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Dogs look fluffy and adorable at that time, and they smell good!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Biscuit and I talk about scents we like.
Hmm... Conversation with Nero flows naturally. I can even tell her about my worries.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: But Leona always gives off the distinctive aura of a lion...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: It makes her feel a bit scary... and aloof.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I know that Leona isn't scary at all and that I shouldn't be feeling this way...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: But I can't help it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: What should I do to overcome this?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Try roaring as you speak.
Try covering your eyes as you speak.
R-roaring...?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Good morning, Leona! Roar!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: What did you—Roar! —do today?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: It... It feels a bit strange!!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Cover my eyes?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Hmm... That seems like a good idea!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: If I don't see Leona's lion-like appearance...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Maybe I'll feel less scared!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Thank you, Trainer!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I talk to Biscuit about overcoming her fear of her friend.
I feel so happy when I'm with Nero!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Her triangular ears are so cute, and her smooth tail is super adorable!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: The same thing goes for other cats. Why are they so lovely?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Because they are born lovely.
You won't think that way if you see cats making trouble...
Right?! These sweet cats are perfect!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Aww, they're so cute.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Hehe, I'm going to visit Nero after today's counseling.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: What? Cats making trouble?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: What trouble?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I never saw Nero making any trouble...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I chat with Biscuit about how adorable cats are.
Someone said that...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: they want to understand what dogs are saying.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: How about you, Trainer? Do you also want to understand them?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I can already understand what you're saying.
I do wish I can do that when they're sick.
Huh? Me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Of course you can understand me...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Ooh... I can communicate with dogs and pass you their message.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: So I'm the interpreter. I can help you understand them...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: That's right...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Yes! Everyone says that
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: they don't know what's wrong with dogs when they're ill,
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: so they want to be able to understand what their dogs are saying.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Hehe. But as long as you have me, I can tell you what the dogs are saying.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: What's ailing them, what they want to do... If you want to find out, feel free to ask me anytime!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I listen to Biscuit talk about the language and behavior of dogs.
Trainer!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Biscuit's eyes sparkle as she wags her tail vigorously.
Uh... Trainer, what kind of person do you see me as?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: A cool and mighty puppy.
A troublemaker of a puppy.
Cool and mighty... Hehehe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Biscuit's tail begins wagging even more rapidly.
I know you said that to make me feel good.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: But still, I'm so happy! Hehe!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: M-me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Troublemaker...?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Biscuit's tail droops.
Really? Are you sure?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: ... I'm just kidding.
Biscuit and I have a short discussion about leaving impressions on others.
Hmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Biscuit stares at the snacks and the ball on the table.
Hmmmmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Biscuit, catch!
Do you want some snacks?
I throw the ball toward the door.
Huh? Oh? Okay!!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Biscuit brings the ball back.
*Huff, huff* I was surprised when you suddenly threw the ball.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I was already hungry. Now I'm starving...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Uhh... I didn't plan to eat any snacks, but it seems like I have to now.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: H-how did you know I want snacks?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Ah, is it because I was staring hard at them? Hehehe...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I planned to cut down on snacks cause I feel like I'm eating too much lately...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: But now that it's in front of me, I'm craving it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Just have one. That should be okay.
Really...? Can I really have one?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I feed Biscuit some snacks.
Trainer...
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Do you like dogs or cats more?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Dogs.
Cats.
Hehe. Really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I like dogs more, too!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: But of course, I like cats a lot as well...!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Wow...! I see. I like cats, too!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Then... do you not like dogs?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Not even a bit...?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Biscuit and I talk about our favorite animals.
The dogs at the shelter are seriously so cute!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I hope they can be happy forever. Hehe.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I hope you can be happy too, Biscuit.
They will be, since you're here.
Hehe! I'm already very happy!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I have Nero by my side, and Leona!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: And you, Trainer!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Really? That would be great!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I'm also very happy because of them!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Biscuit and I talk about happiness.
The dogs at the shelter hate having their teeth brushed.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: What should I do to give their teeth a good brush?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: You can just lead by example.
How about giving them snacks after brushing their teeth?
I also don't like brushing my teeth though...!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: ... But I do have to set a good example, right...?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: ... I wonder if there is snack-flavored toothpaste?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Wow! That's a wonderful idea, Trainer!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I can teach them while giving them snacks! Win-win!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Hehe. If I brush my teeth properly, will you also give me snacks?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I pick out some yummy toothpaste with Biscuit.
*Gurgle*
... Oof!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Trainer... I'm hungry.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Give her chocolate.
Give her sweet potato sticks.
Chocolates... are not my cup of tea, sorry.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Biscuit's tail starts wagging quickly.
*Drool*
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: This is my favorite... I can eat it, right?!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I give Biscuit her favorite snack and spend some time with her.
There's a new puppy at the shelter, but it's very shy!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: How can I get to know it better?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Be patient and wait until it approaches you.
Why don't you try approaching it, Biscuit?
Yeah... I want to play with it right away...!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: Hehe. But I have to give it some time, right?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: After all, it's still unfamiliar with this place...!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I hope the puppy opens its heart soon!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I went up to it when it arrived, but it turned and hid in the corner...!
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: What if it gets more afraid of me?
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I should just watch from afar and wait until it gets used to being here.
adviseScripts.speaker: Biscuit

adviseScripts.text: I listen to Biscuit talk about the new puppy.
